## The Event Flow Pipeline

This is THE most important thing to understand.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 1. DSL (Author Time) │
│ b.at(1000).receive({ from: "John", text: "Hello!" }) │
│ │
│ ↓ generates │
│ │
│ 2. IR Event (Intermediate Representation) │
│ { kind: "APP", appId: "app_{{ snakeCase name }}", type: "MESSAGE_RECEIVED", │
│ payload: { from: "John", text: "Hello!", conversationId: "..." }} │
│ │
│ ↓ lowering (compiler) │
│ │
│ 3. RuntimeEvent (What the engine sees) │
│ { at: 1000, kind: "APP", appId: "app_{{ snakeCase name }}", │
│ type: "MESSAGE_RECEIVED", conversationId: "...", from: "John" } │
│ │
│ ↓ dispatched by TokovoEngine │
│ │
│ 4. Reducer (State Machine) │
│ reducer(worldState, event) → worldState with new message │
│ │
│ ↓ state change │
│ │
│ 5. Layout Engine │
│ computeChatLayout(state) → { messageLayouts, scrollY, ... } │
│ │
│ ↓ positions │
│ │
│ 6. React Components │
│
<MessageBubble y={layout.y} height={layout.height} /> │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

