## Anchors & Camera System

### What Are Anchors?

Anchors are **named regions** that the camera can target.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ ┌─── "header" ───────────────────────┐ │
│ │ Profile Picture Chat Name │ │
│ └────────────────────────────────────┘ │
│ │
│ ┌──── "msg_1" (message) ────┐ │
│ │ Hello! │ │
│ └───────────────────────────┘ │
│ │
│ ┌──── "msg_2" (message)│
│ │ Hi there! │
│ └──────────────────────│
│ │
│ ┌──── "typing" ────┐ │
│ │ • • • │ │
│ └──────────────────┘ │
│ │
│ ┌─── "input" ────────────────────────┐ │
│ │ Type a message... │ │
│ └────────────────────────────────────┘ │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### DSL Usage

```typescript
// Focus on last message
b.at(1000).camera.focus("lastMessage");

// Pan to header
b.at(2000).camera.pan("header");

// Zoom with shake
b.at(3000).camera.focus("lastMessage", { shot: "CLOSEUP", shake: 0.3 });
```

### How Anchors Are Computed

```typescript
// runtime/adapters/anchors.ts
getAnchors(world, layout, deviceId) {
const regions = layout.semantic.regions;
const anchors = {};

// Map regions to anchors
for (const [key, region] of Object.entries(regions)) {
anchors[key] = region.rect; // { x, y, width, height }
}

// Computed aliases
if (layout.meta?.lastMessageId) {
anchors["lastMessage"] = regions[layout.meta.lastMessageId].rect;
}

return { anchors, deviceId, appId: "app_{{ snakeCase name }}" };
}
```

### Anchor Framing

Each anchor type has framing parameters:

```typescript
// How the camera frames each anchor type
const ANCHOR_FRAMING = {
message: { anchorPoint: { x: 0.5, y: 0.5 }, paddingPx: 40, targetFill: 0.6 },
typing: { anchorPoint: { x: 0.35, y: 0.5 }, paddingPx: 30, targetFill: 0.3 },
profile: { anchorPoint: { x: 0.2, y: 0.15 }, paddingPx: 50, targetFill: 0.4 },
};
```

