## Widgets & Slots

### What Are Widgets?

Widgets are **DSL-controllable UI elements** beyond messages:

- Status bar (time, battery, signal)
- Keyboard (visible, typing animation)
- Notifications (heads-up, lock screen)
- System UI (control center, action sheets)

### What Are Slots?

Slots are **placeholder regions** where content can be rendered:

```
┌────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ [STATUS_BAR slot] │ ← Time, battery, signal
├────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ [HEADER slot] │ ← App header
├────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ │
│ [CONTENT slot] │ ← Messages, content
│ │
├────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ [INPUT slot] │ ← Text input
├────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ [KEYBOARD slot] │ ← On-screen keyboard
└────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### DSL Control

Every visible element should be controllable:

```typescript
// Good: DSL controls everything
b.at(1000).keyboard.show();
b.at(1500).keyboard.type("Hello");
b.at(2000).notification.show({ title: "New message", body: "..." });

// Bad: Hard-coded in component
const [showKeyboard, setShowKeyboard] = useState(false); // ❌ No DSL control!
```

### Design Principle

> **If it's visible, it comes from WorldState.**
> **If it changes, it's an Event.**

